<subSubSection id="C37398FDFF9AFF98FF63809DB77EF864" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD6CB76FF9AFF98FF63809DB6CEF8DC" blockId="3.[151,1437,1060,1987]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FF63809DB545FA48" bold="true" box="[199,315,1492,1518]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF9AFF98FEE1809DB62EFA48" authorityName="sensu Athias-Henriot" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="McGregor" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[325,592,1492,1518]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FEE1809DB62EFA48" box="[325,592,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Neoseiulus californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recently redescribed in detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF9AFF98FBE2809DB158FA48" author="Tixier, M-S. &amp; Guichou, S. &amp; Kreiter, K." box="[1094,1318,1492,1519]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" pagination="453 - 469" refId="ref16843" refString="Tixier, M-S., Guichou, S. &amp; Kreiter, K. (2008) Morphological variation in the biological control agent Neoseiulus californicus (McGregor) (Acari: Phytoseiidae): consequences for diagnostic reliability and synonymies. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 453 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 07052" type="journal article" year="2008">
Tixier 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FB30809CB0B6FA48" box="[1172,1224,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF9AFF98FA91809CB49CF9B4" author="Xu, X. &amp; Wang, B. &amp; Wang, E. &amp; Zhang, Z. - Q." pageId="3" pageNumber="526" pagination="329 - 344" refId="ref17321" refString="Xu, X., Wang, B., Wang, E. &amp; Zhang, Z. - Q. (2013) Comments on the identity of Neoseiulus californicus sensu lato (Acari: Phytoseiidae) with a redescription of this species from Southern China. Systematic &amp; Applied Acarology, 18, 329 - 344. https: // doi. org / 10.11158 / saa. 18.4.3" type="journal article" year="2013">
Xu 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FAC5809CB1EBFA48" box="[1377,1429,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF9AFF98FEBD80B1B647F9B4" author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Beard, J. J." box="[281,569,1528,1554]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" pagination="451 - 507" refId="ref13979" refString="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Beard, J. J. (2018) Acarine biocontrol agents Neoseiulus californicus sensu Athias-Henriot (1977) and N. barkeri Hughes (Mesostigmata: Phytoseiidae) redescribed, their synonymies assessed, and the identity of N. californicus (McGregor) clarified based on examination of types. Zootaxa, 4500 (4), 451 - 507. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4500.4.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Beaulieu &amp; Beard (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. The taxonomical identity of this species has suffered a rocambolesque story. Originally described by McGregor in 1954 from a single male, the type was lost for a very long time. Recently, the original male was found and examined revealing that the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF9AFF98FCC78309B0F1F9FC" authorityName="McGregor" authorityYear="1954" box="[867,1167,1600,1626]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Typhlodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FCC78309B0F1F9FC" box="[867,1167,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Typhlodromus californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by McGregor does not match with the present concept of the species not with the identity of the species commercialized under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF9AFF98FF7883C1B522F904" box="[220,348,1672,1698]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Amblyseius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FF7883C1B522F904" box="[220,348,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Amblyseius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF9AFF98FE2183C1B6F0F904" authorityName="sensu Athias-Henriot" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="McGregor" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[389,654,1672,1698]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FE2183C1B6F0F904" box="[389,654,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Neoseiulus californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for biological control purposes (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF9AFF98FBA083C1B15EF904" author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Beard, J. J." box="[1028,1312,1672,1698]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" pagination="451 - 507" refId="ref13979" refString="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Beard, J. J. (2018) Acarine biocontrol agents Neoseiulus californicus sensu Athias-Henriot (1977) and N. barkeri Hughes (Mesostigmata: Phytoseiidae) redescribed, their synonymies assessed, and the identity of N. californicus (McGregor) clarified based on examination of types. Zootaxa, 4500 (4), 451 - 507. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4500.4.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Beaulieu &amp; Beard, 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Although it is clear that the specimen used by McGregor to describe the species belongs, in fact, to another previously described taxon, (
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF9AFF98FEC48399B6E8F94D" authority="Hughes" authorityName="Hughes" authorityYear="1948" box="[352,662,1744,1771]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barkeri">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FEC48399B64AF94C" box="[352,564,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Neoseiulus barkeri</emphasis>
Hughes
</taxonomicName>
), a proposal was sent to the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF9AFF98FEE283BDB64CF8A8" author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Beard, J. J. &amp; McMurtry, J. A. &amp; Zhang, Z-Q." box="[326,562,1780,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" pagination="103 - 113" refId="ref14059" refString="Beaulieu, F., Beard, J. J., McMurtry, J. A. &amp; Zhang, Z-Q. (2019) Case 3780 - Typhlodromus californicus McGregor, 1954 (currently Neoseiulus californicus; Arachnida, Acari, Mesostigmata, Phytoseiidae): proposed conservation of current usage by designation of a neotype. The Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature, 76, 103 - 113. https: // doi. org / 10.21805 / bzn. v 76. a 032" type="journal article" year="2019">
Beaulieu 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FE1183BCB596F8A8" box="[437,488,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
) requiring the conservation of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF9AFF98FBA283BDB0F2F8A8" authorityName="sensu Athias-Henriot" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="McGregor" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[1030,1164,1780,1806]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF9AFF98FBA283BDB0F2F8A8" box="[1030,1164,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the designation of a 
<typeStatus id="54D275D4FF9AFF98FF338250B48EF895" box="[151,240,1817,1843]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">neotype</typeStatus>
which is compatible with the species concept of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF9AFF98FCB18251B06EF894" author="Athias-Henriot, C." box="[789,1040,1816,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" pagination="61 - 73" refId="ref13884" refString="Athias-Henriot, C. (1977) Nouvelles notes sur les Amblyseiini. III. Sur le genre Cydnodromus: Redefinition, composition (Parasitiformes, Phytoseiidae). Entomophaga, 22, 61 - 73. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02372991" type="journal article" year="1977">Athias-Henriot (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, with the current common usage of the name in the literature and with the populations produced by commercial companies and released in the field to control spider mites and other small arthropods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD6CB76FF9AFF98FF6382CDB77EF864" blockId="3.[151,1437,1060,1987]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">
Setal measurements and other morphological traits of the females collected match with the data provided in the most recent redescription by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF9AFF98FE7882E1B685F864" author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Beard, J. J." box="[476,763,1960,1986]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" pagination="451 - 507" refId="ref13979" refString="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Beard, J. J. (2018) Acarine biocontrol agents Neoseiulus californicus sensu Athias-Henriot (1977) and N. barkeri Hughes (Mesostigmata: Phytoseiidae) redescribed, their synonymies assessed, and the identity of N. californicus (McGregor) clarified based on examination of types. Zootaxa, 4500 (4), 451 - 507. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4500.4.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Beaulieu &amp; Beard (2018)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
